are ultimately inconclusive.

1182
01:13:54,503 --> 01:13:58,200
A point I'm confident you’ll illustrate
to the court under cross-examination.

1183
01:13:58,273 --> 01:14:01,436
So I'm sure you won't mind
if his opinion is admitted now.

1184
01:14:01,510 --> 01:14:03,273
Not at all, sir.

1185
01:14:05,781 --> 01:14:09,945
Dr. Stone, did Willie Santiago
die of poisoning?

1186
01:14:10,018 --> 01:14:11,713
Absolutely.

1187
01:14:11,787 --> 01:14:15,883
You're aware that the lab and coroner's
report show no traces of poison?

1188
01:14:15,958 --> 01:14:18,483
- Yes, I am.
- Then how do you justify-

1189
01:14:18,560 --> 01:14:21,529
There are literally dozens of toxins
which are virtually undetectable...

1190
01:14:21,597 --> 01:14:24,259
both in the human body
and on a fabric.

1191
01:14:24,333 --> 01:14:27,996
The nature of the acidosis
is the compelling factor on this issue.

1192
01:14:28,871 --> 01:14:30,771
Thank you, sir.

1193
01:14:32,708 --> 01:14:36,041
Commander, is it possible for a person
to have an affliction-

1194
01:14:36,111 --> 01:14:40,480
some sort of condition- which might
speed up the process of acidosis?

1195
01:14:43,218 --> 01:14:45,083
Commander, is it possible?

1196
01:14:45,153 --> 01:14:47,018
It's possible.

1197
01:14:47,089 --> 01:14:49,489
What might some of those
conditions be?

1198
01:14:50,559 --> 01:14:53,050
If a person had a coronary disorder...

1199
01:14:53,128 --> 01:14:56,188
or a cerebral disorder,
the process would be more rapid.

1200
01:14:56,265 --> 01:15:00,292
If I had a coronary condition and
a clean rag was placed in my mouth...

1201
01:15:00,369 --> 01:15:04,135
and the rag was pushed too far down,
is it possible that my cells...

1202
01:15:04,206 --> 01:15:06,970
would continue burning sugar
after the rag was taken out?

1203
01:15:07,042 --> 01:15:09,943
It would have to be
a very serious condition.

1204
01:15:10,012 --> 01:15:12,276
Is it possible to have
a serious coronary condition...

1205
01:15:12,347 --> 01:15:15,783
where the warning signals were so mild
as to escape a physician...

1206
01:15:15,851 --> 01:15:18,376
during a routine medical exam?

1207
01:15:18,453 --> 01:15:21,718
Possibly. There would still
be symptoms, though.

1208
01:15:21,790 --> 01:15:24,122
- What kind of symptoms?
- There are hundreds-

1209
01:15:24,192 --> 01:15:26,490
- Chest pains?
- Yes.

1210
01:15:26,562 --> 01:15:28,496
- Shortness of breath?
- Yes.

1211
01:15:28,564 --> 01:15:30,998
- Fatigue?
- Of course.

1212
01:15:36,605 --> 01:15:38,539
Doctor, is this your signature?

1213
01:15:40,175 --> 01:15:41,301
Yes, it is.

1214
01:15:42,044 --> 01:15:45,707
