for five minutes...

1335
01:23:31,379 --> 01:23:33,973
then they poured glue on my hands.

1336
01:23:34,049 --> 01:23:37,746
And it worked too, 'cause
I ain't never dropped my weapon since.

1337
01:23:39,220 --> 01:23:42,280
Was Private Santiago ever late
for platoon meetings?

1338
01:23:42,357 --> 01:23:43,517
Yes, sir.

1339
01:23:43,591 --> 01:23:45,957
- Was his barracks ever in disorder?
- Yes, sir.

1340
01:23:46,027 --> 01:23:48,359
- Did he ever fall back on a run?
- All the time, sir.

1341
01:23:48,430 --> 01:23:53,800
Did he ever, prior to the night
of September 6, receive a Code Red?

1342
01:23:53,868 --> 01:23:55,358
No, sir.

1343
01:23:55,437 --> 01:23:57,496
- Never?
- No, sir.

1344
01:23:59,174 --> 01:24:01,540
You got a Code Red
'cause your palms were sweaty.

1345
01:24:01,609 --> 01:24:05,670
Why didn't Santiago,
this burden to his unit, ever get one?

1346
01:24:07,148 --> 01:24:09,173
Dawson wouldn't allow it, sir.

1347
01:24:10,285 --> 01:24:12,344
Dawson wouldn't allow it.

1348
01:24:12,420 --> 01:24:16,015
