- Till the fat lady sings.

1391
01:26:50,812 --> 01:26:52,746
Walked into that one.

1392
01:27:04,292 --> 01:27:07,022
Oh, Jesus Christ!

1393
01:27:07,095 --> 01:27:09,757
You left the door unlocked.

1394
01:27:09,831 --> 01:27:12,891
- You scared the shit out of me.
-Just keep driving.

1395
01:27:12,967 --> 01:27:14,901
Are you aware
you're under subpoena?

1396
01:27:14,969 --> 01:27:18,769
Yes. I'm also aware that the lives
of two Marines are in your hands.

1397
01:27:18,840 --> 01:27:21,001
If there was something
I could do about that, I would.

1398
01:27:21,075 --> 01:27:23,475
But since I can't,
all I can do is help you.

1399
01:27:23,544 --> 01:27:25,876
- What do you know?
- I know everything.

1400
01:27:25,947 --> 01:27:28,177
- Was it a Code Red?
- Yes.

1401
01:27:28,249 --> 01:27:30,376
- Did Kendrick give the order?
- Yes.

1402
01:27:30,451 --> 01:27:33,386
- Did you witness it?
- I didn't need to.

1403
01:27:33,454 --> 01:27:36,082
Then how do you know?
- I know. - You know shit.

1404
01:27:36,157 --> 01:27:38,523
He was never gonna be transferred
off that base.

1405
01:27:44,465 --> 01:27:47,764
Jessup was gonna keep him on the base.
He said he wanted him trained.

1406
01:27:47,835 --> 01:27:50,429
- The transfer order has your signature.
- Yeah, I know.

1407
01:27:50,505 --> 01:27:54,464
I signed it the morning you arrived
in Cuba, five days after Santiago died.

1408
01:27:58,146 --> 01:28:00,910
I'm gonna get you a deal, some kind
of immunity with the prosecutor.

1409
01:28:00,982 --> 01:28:05,476
In about four days, you'll appear
as a witness and tell what you know.

1410
01:28:05,553 --> 01:28:09,182
I'm gonna check you into a motel.
We are gonna start from the beginning.

1411
01:28:09,257 --> 01:28:13,421
I don't want a deal,
and I don't want immunity.

1412
01:28:13,494 --> 01:28:18,727
I want you to know that I'm proud
neither of what I've done or am doing.

1413
01:28:21,069 --> 01:28:23,037
- Where is he?
- The Downtown Lodge in Northeast.

1414
01:28:23,104 --> 01:28:25,231
- I want him guarded.
- That's a good idea.

1415
01:28:25,306 --> 01:28:28,002
- My clearance code is 411527273.
- Clearance code?

1416
01:28:28,076 --> 01:28:30,738
- Thank you.
- Do you have a clearance code?

1417
01:28:30,812 --> 01:28:32,939
This is Jo Galloway.
I need to secure a witness.

1418
01:28:33,014 --> 01:28:35,983
Anyway, he also said that Jessup’s lying
about the transportation off the base.

1419
01:28:36,050 --> 01:28:38,848
Jessup said that 6:00 the next morning
was the first flight Santiago could have left on.

1420
01:28:38,920 --> 01:28:42,412
Markinson says there was a plane
that left seven hours earlier.

1421
01:28:42,490 --> 01:28:45,516
That was impressive. Did you hear
what I said about the flight?

1422
01:28:45,593 --> 01:28:48,858
Sam, when a flight takes off,
there's a record kept, right?

1423
01:28:48,930 --> 01:28:51,125
Yeah, you need the tower chief’s log
from Gitmo.

1424
01:28:51,199 --> 01:28:54,327
- Get it.
- We're gonna win.

1425
01:28:54,402 --> 01:28:56,768
We don't know who Markinson is.
We don't know what the logbook will say.

1426
01:28:56,838 --> 01:28:59,864
You just concentrate on Downey.
I'm gonna talk to Ross and tell him where we are.

1427
01:29:06,981 --> 01:29:10,417
Nice work today.
Redirect on Barnes.

1428
01:29:10,485 --> 01:29:14,615
- I have Markinson.
- Where is he?

1429
01:29:14,689 --> 01:29:19,023
Motel room in Northeast with
six Federal Marshalls outside his door.

1430
01:29:19,093 --> 01:29:21,254
The transfer that Markinson
signed is phony.

1431
01:29:21,329 --> 01:29:24,162
Jessup's statement that the 6:00 a. m.
flight was the first available is a lie.

1432
01:29:24,232 --> 01:29:26,666
We're checking the tower chief’s log.
I'd like a beer, please.

1433
01:29:26,734 --> 01:29:31,171
In the meantime, I'm gonna put Kendrick
on the stand and have some fun.

1434
01:29:31,239 --> 01:29:34,003
All right, I have
an obligation to tell you...

1435
01:29:34,075 --> 01:29:37,169
that if you accuse Kendrick or Jessup
of any crime without proper evidence...

1436
01:29:37,245 --> 01:29:40,009
you'll be subject to a court-martial
for professional misconduct.

1437
01:29:40,081 --> 01:29:44,575
That's something that'll be stapled to
every job application you ever fill out.

1438
01:29:46,254 --> 01:29:49,815
Markinson's not gonna hold up, Danny.
He's a crazy man.

1439
01:29:49,891 --> 01:29:53,520
I'm not saying this to intimidate you.
I'm being your lawyer here.

1440
01:29:53,594 --> 01:29:57,690
Thanks, Jack. And I think the fucking
bunch of you are certifiably insane.

1441
01:29:57,765 --> 01:30:00,097
Your code of honor makes me
want to beat the shit out of somebody.

1442
01:30:00,168 --> 01:30:04,036
Don't lump me in with them
just because we wear the same uniform.

1443
01:30:04,105 --> 01:30:07,165
I'm your friend, and I don't think
your clients belong in jail...

1444
01:30:07,241 --> 01:30:09,175
but I don't get
to make that decision.

1445
01:30:09,243 --> 01:30:13,646
I represent the United States government
without passion or prejudice.

1446
01:30:13,714 --> 01:30:17,047
- My client has a case.
- Here you go.

1447
01:30:20,888 --> 01:30:23,686
I want you to acknowledge that
the judge advocate has made you aware...

1448
01:30:23,758 --> 01:30:26,625
of the possible consequences involved
in accusing a Marine officer...

1449
01:30:26,694 --> 01:30:28,787
of a felony
without proper evidence.

1450
01:30:28,863 --> 01:30:31,525
I've been so advised.

1451
01:30:35,736 --> 01:30:38,534
You got bullied
into that courtroom, Danny.

1452
01:30:38,606 --> 01:30:42,474
By everyone.
By Dawson, by Galloway.

1453
01:30:42,543 --> 01:30:45,103
Shit, I practically dared you.

1454
01:30:46,280 --> 01:30:49,807
You got bullied into that courtroom
by the memory of a dead lawyer.

1455
01:30:55,923 --> 01:30:59,051
You're a lousy fucking
softball player, Jack!

1456
01:31:02,430 --> 01:31:06,594
Your boys are going down, Danny.
I can't stop it anymore.

1457
01:31:11,906 --> 01:31:15,239
Lieutenant Kendrick, in your opinion,
was Private Santiago a good Marine?

1458
01:31:15,309 --> 01:31:17,402
I'd say he was about average.

1459
01:31:17,478 --> 01:31:20,879
You signed three proficiency
and conduct reports on Santiago.

1460
01:31:20,948 --> 01:31:24,611
On all three reports, you indicate
a rating of below average.

1461
01:31:27,989 --> 01:31:31,925
Yes, Private Santiago
was below average.

1462
01:31:31,993 --> 01:31:35,759
I did not see the need
to trample on a man's grave.

1463
01:31:35,830 --> 01:31:37,991
We appreciate that,
but you’re under oath now.

1464
01:31:38,065 --> 01:31:40,693
Unpleasant as it may be,
we'd all just as soon hear the truth.

1465
01:31:40,768 --> 01:31:42,633
I'm aware of my oath.

1466
01:31:42,703 --> 01:31:47,663
These are the last three pro-con reports
you signed for Lance Corporal Dawson.

1467
01:31:47,742 --> 01:31:49,676
Dawson received
two marks of exceptional...

1468
01:31:49,744 --> 01:31:54,113
but on this most recent report of June 9
he received a rating of below average.

1469
01:31:54,181 --> 01:31:58,174
- I'd like to discuss this last report.
- That would be fine.

1470
01:31:58,252 --> 01:32:01,915
Lance Corporal Dawson's ranking after
the school of infantry was perfect.

1471
01:32:01,989 --> 01:32:04,924
Over half that class has since
been promoted to full corporal...

1472
01:32:04,992 --> 01:32:07,290
while Dawson has remained
a lance corporal.

1473
01:32:07,361 --> 01:32:10,353
Was Dawson's promotion held up
because of this last report?

1474
01:32:10,431 --> 01:32:12,365
I'm sure it was.

1475
01:32:12,433 --> 01:32:15,425
Do you recall why Dawson was given
such a poor grade on this report?

1476
01:32:15,503 --> 01:32:16,800
I'm sure I don't.

1477
01:32:16,871 --> 01:32:20,705
I have many men in my charge.
I write many reports.

1478
01:32:20,775 --> 01:32:26,543
Lieutenant, do you recall an incident
involving a P.F.C. Curtis Bell...

1479
01:32:26,614 --> 01:32:29,344
who'd been found stealing liquor
from the Officers' Club?

1480
01:32:29,417 --> 01:32:31,317
Yes, I do.

1481
01:32:31,385 --> 01:32:33,819
Did you report Private Bell
to proper authorities?

1482
01:32:35,723 --> 01:32:37,884
I have two books at my bedside-

1483
01:32:37,959 --> 01:32:40,951
The Marine Corps Code of Conduct
and The King James Bible.

1484
01:32:41,028 --> 01:32:43,622
The only proper authorities I'm aware of
are my commanding officer...

1485
01:32:43,698 --> 01:32:46,360
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup
and the Lord our God.

1486
01:32:47,969 --> 01:32:50,529
At your request, Lieutenant Kendrick,
I can have the record reflect...

1487
01:32:50,605 --> 01:32:53,267
your lack of acknowledgement
of this court as a proper authority.

1488
01:32:53,341 --> 01:32:56,174
- Objection. Argumentative.
- Sustained.

1489
01:32:56,243 --> 01:32:58,336
Watch yourself, counselor.

1490
01:32:58,412 --> 01:33:01,108
Did you report Private Bell
to your superiors?

1491
01:33:01,182 --> 01:33:03,946
I remember thinking very highly
of Private Bell-

1492
01:33:04,018 --> 01:33:07,181
not wanting to see his record tarnished
by a formal charge.

1493
01:33:08,356 --> 01:33:11,223
You preferred it be handled
within the unit?

1494
01:33:12,960 --> 01:33:14,894
Yes, I most certainly did.

1495
01:33:16,130 --> 01:33:19,361
- Do you know what a Code Red is?
- Yes, I do.

1496
01:33:19,433 --> 01:33:22,630
- Have you ever ordered a Code Red?
- No, I have not.

1497
01:33:22,703 --> 01:33:25,797
Did you order Dawson and two other men
to make sure that Private Bell...

1498
01:33:25,873 --> 01:33:31,311
received no food or drink, except water,
for a period of seven days?

1499
01:33:31,379 --> 01:33:33,677
That is a distortion
of the truth, Lieutenant.

1500
01:33:33,748 --> 01:33:36,012
Private Bell was placed
on barracks restriction.

1501
01:33:36,083 --> 01:33:39,177
He was given water and vitamin
supplements, and I can assure you...

1502
01:33:39,253 --> 01:33:43,212
at no time
was his health in danger.

1503
01:33:43,290 --> 01:33:46,020
I'm sure it was lovely
for Private Bell.

1504
01:33:46,093 --> 01:33:48,755
But you did order
the barracks restriction, didn’t you?

1505
01:33:48,829 --> 01:33:52,993
- You did order the denial of food?
- Yes, I did.

1506
01:33:53,067 --> 01:33:56,867
Wouldn't this form of discipline
be considered a Code Red?

1507
01:33:57,868 --> 01:33:58,868
No.

1508
01:33:59,674 --> 01:34:03,542
If I called the other 478 Marines
at Guantanamo Bay to testify...

1509
01:34:03,611 --> 01:34:05,704
would they consider it
a Code Red?

1510
01:34:05,780 --> 01:34:09,739
The witness can't possibly testify
as to what 478 other men would say.

1511
01:34:09,817 --> 01:34:13,685
We object to this entire line
of questioning. It's argumentative...

1512
01:34:13,754 --> 01:34:16,120
and irrelevant badgering
of the witness.

1513
01:34:16,190 --> 01:34:18,818
The government's objection
is sustained, Lieutenant Kaffee...

1514
01:34:18,893 --> 01:34:22,021
and I would remind you that you’re now
questioning a Marine officer...

1515
01:34:22,096 --> 01:34:24,223
with an impeccable service record.

1516
01:34:24,298 --> 01:34:25,856
Thank you, Your Honor.

1517
01:34:26,934 --> 01:34:30,734
Lieutenant, was Dawson given a rating
of below average on this last report...

1518
01:34:30,805 --> 01:34:33,672
because you learned he'd been sneaking
food to Private Bell?

1519
01:34:33,741 --> 01:34:37,006
- Object!
- Not so fast. Lieutenant?

1520
01:34:38,679 --> 01:34:42,342
Lance Corporal Dawson
was given a below average rating...

1521
01:34:43,317 --> 01:34:45,785
because he had committed a crime.

1522
01:34:45,853 --> 01:34:49,118
A crime?
What crime did he commit?

1523
01:34:53,027 --> 01:34:58,795
Dawson brought a hungry guy some food.
What crime did he commit?

1524
01:35:00,801 --> 01:35:02,359
He disobeyed an order.

1525
01:35:02,436 --> 01:35:04,927
And because he exercised
his own set of values...

1526
01:35:05,005 --> 01:35:07,997
because he made a decision
about the welfare of a Marine...

1527
01:35:08,075 --> 01:35:11,704
that was in conflict with your order,
he was punished, is that right?

1528
01:35:11,779 --> 01:35:15,306
Lance Corporal Dawson
disobeyed an order.

1529
01:35:15,382 --> 01:35:17,907
Yeah, but it wasn't
a real order, was it?

1530
01:35:17,985 --> 01:35:20,180
After all, it's peacetime.

1531
01:35:20,254 --> 01:35:23,519
He wasn't being asked to secure a hill
or advance on a beachhead.

1532
01:35:23,591 --> 01:35:28,028
I mean, surely a Marine
of Dawson's intelligence...

1533
01:35:28,095 --> 01:35:31,189
can be trusted to determine on his own
which are the important orders...

1534
01:35:31,265 --> 01:35:35,167
and which orders might, say,
be morally questionable?

1535
01:35:38,405 --> 01:35:40,202
Can he?

1536
01:35:40,274 --> 01:35:43,937
Can Dawson determine on his own
which orders he's going to follow?

1537
01:35:44,011 --> 01:35:45,706
No, he cannot.

1538
01:35:45,780 --> 01:35:48,510
A lesson he learned
after the Curtis Bell incident, right?

1539
01:35:48,582 --> 01:35:51,449
- I would think so.
- You know so, don’t you?

1540
01:35:51,519 --> 01:35:53,214
- Object!
- Sustained.

1541
01:35:55,256 --> 01:35:58,191
Lieutenant Kendrick,
one final question.

1542
01:35:59,493 --> 01:36:02,792
If you had ordered Dawson
to give Santiago a Code Red-

1543
01:36:02,863 --> 01:36:07,095
- I specifically ordered those men-
- Would he disobey you again?

1544
01:36:07,168 --> 01:36:11,229
- Lieutenant, don't answer that!
- You don't have to. I'm through.

1545
01:36:11,305 --> 01:36:14,934
Lieutenant Kendrick, did you order
Lance Corporal Dawson...

1546
01:36:15,009 --> 01:36:18,968
and Private Downey
to give Willie Santiago a Code Red?

1547
01:36:22,183 --> 01:36:25,152
- No, I did not.
- Thank you.

1548
01:36:29,123 --> 01:36:31,284
What's the word?

1549
01:36:31,358 --> 01:36:35,624
I got the tower chief’s log from that
night. Jessup’s telling the truth.

1550
01:36:35,696 --> 01:36:39,928
- 6:00 a. m. flight was the first plane.
- Let me see this.

1551
01:36:50,110 --> 01:36:52,977
- Working late tonight?
- Oh, yeah.

1552
01:36:57,351 --> 01:37:01,048
There wasn't a flight at 11:00.
What the fuck are you trying to pull?

1553
01:37:01,121 --> 01:37:04,352
The first flight stateside
left Guantanamo Bay at 2300.

1554
01:37:04,425 --> 01:37:08,361
It arrived at Andrews Air Force Base
at a few minutes past 2:00.

1555
01:37:08,429 --> 01:37:11,626
Really? Then why isn't it
listed in the tower chief’s log?

1556
01:37:13,734 --> 01:37:15,031
Jessup.

1557
01:37:15,102 --> 01:37:17,536
What are you telling me?
He fixed the logbook?

1558
01:37:19,573 --> 01:37:23,600
Maybe he can make it so a plane didn't
take off, but I can prove one landed.

1559
01:37:23,677 --> 01:37:25,770
I'll get the logbook from Andrews.

1560
01:37:25,846 --> 01:37:28,815
You're not gonna find anything
in the Andrews logbook, either.

1561
01:37:28,883 --> 01:37:30,817
He can make
an entire flight disappear?

1562
01:37:30,885 --> 01:37:35,379
Jessup is about to be appointed director
of operations for the Security Council.

1563
01:37:35,456 --> 01:37:39,449
You don't get to that position without
knowing how to sidestep some land mines.

1564
01:37:39,526 --> 01:37:42,393
He's not gonna be able
to sidestep you.

1565
01:37:42,463 --> 01:37:44,863
You don't still intend
to put me on the stand?

1566
01:37:44,932 --> 01:37:47,867
Thursday morning, 10:00.

1567
01:37:52,306 --> 01:37:56,140
There's gotta be someone
who can testify to the flight.

1568
01:37:56,210 --> 01:37:59,441
This isn't TWA.
There isn't a regular flight schedule.

1569
01:37:59,513 --> 01:38:02,311
Do you have any idea how many planes
take off and land every day?

1570
01:38:02,383 --> 01:38:05,819
A ground crew kid won't remember
a flight that landed four weeks ago.

1571
01:38:05,886 --> 01:38:09,049
- How do you know if you don't check?
- Forget the flight!

1572
01:38:09,123 --> 01:38:12,923
Markinson will testify that Jessup
refused to transfer Santiago.

1573
01:38:12,993 --> 01:38:15,553
He'll testify to the forged transfer,
and that'll be enough.

1574
01:38:15,629 --> 01:38:18,154
That and Downey's testimony
really ought to be enough.

1575
01:38:23,671 --> 01:38:27,630
Why did you go into Santiago's room
on the night of the 6th?

1576
01:38:27,708 --> 01:38:30,939
To give Private Santiago
a Code Red, ma'am.

1577
01:38:31,011 --> 01:38:33,206
Why did you give him a Code Red?

1578
01:38:33,280 --> 01:38:36,716
I was ordered to give him a Code Red
by the platoon commander...

1579
01:38:36,784 --> 01:38:41,016
of Rifle Security Company Windward,
Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1580
01:38:42,222 --> 01:38:44,622
You're gonna do fine.

1581
01:38:46,226 --> 01:38:48,717
You think they'll let us go back
to our platoon soon, ma'am?

1582
01:38:50,164 --> 01:38:52,064
Absolutely.

1583
01:38:55,269 --> 01:38:57,703
Do you remember the order of questions?
Are you sure?

1584
01:38:57,771 --> 01:39:00,706
And we'll use small words, 'cause he
gets rattled if he doesn't understand.

1585
01:39:00,774 --> 01:39:03,675
- I'm just saying go slow.
- I'm gonna go slow.

1586
01:39:03,744 --> 01:39:06,679
And get him off
as fast as you can.

1587
01:39:06,747 --> 01:39:09,682
What?
It's gonna be fine.

1588
01:39:12,119 --> 01:39:14,087
Dear Mr. and Mrs. Santiago...

1589
01:39:15,422 --> 01:39:17,890
I was William's executive officer.

1590
01:39:17,958 --> 01:39:21,450
I knew your son vaguely,
which is to say I knew his name.

1591
01:39:22,529 --> 01:39:24,520
In a matter of time,
the trial of the two men...

1592
01:39:24,598 --> 01:39:27,294
charged with your son's death
will be concluded...

1593
01:39:27,368 --> 01:39:29,632
and seven men and two women
whom you've never met...

1594
01:39:29,703 --> 01:39:33,696
will try to offer you an explanation
as to why William is dead.

1595
01:39:33,774 --> 01:39:37,403
For my part, I've done as much as I can
to bring the truth to light.

1596
01:39:38,278 --> 01:39:39,802
And the truth is this-

1597
01:39:39,880 --> 01:39:42,440
Your son is dead for only one reason-

1598
01:39:42,516 --> 01:39:45,451
I wasn't strong enough to stop it.

1599
01:39:45,519 --> 01:39:49,922
Always, Lieutenant Colonel
Matthew Andrew Markinson...

1600
01:39:49,990 --> 01:39:51,480
United States Marine Corps.

1601
01:39:56,630 --> 01:40:00,157
Private, I want you
to tell us one last time.

1602
01:40:00,234 --> 01:40:06,070
Why did you go to Private Santiago's
room on the night of September 6?

1603
01:40:06,140 --> 01:40:08,540
A Code Red was ordered
by my platoon commander...

1604
01:40:08,609 --> 01:40:10,941
Lieutenant Jonathan James Kendrick.

1605
01:40:11,512 --> 01:40:13,275
Thank you.

1606
01:40:13,347 --> 01:40:14,939
Your witness.

1607
01:40:19,486 --> 01:40:21,681
Private, the week of 2 September...

1608
01:40:21,755 --> 01:40:25,247
the switch log has you down
at Post 39 until 1600.

1609
01:40:25,325 --> 01:40:26,519
Is that correct?

1610
01:40:26,593 --> 01:40:29,528
I'm sure it is, sir.
They keep that log pretty good.

1611
01:40:29,596 --> 01:40:33,191
How far is it from Post 39
to the Windward Barracks?

1612
01:40:33,267 --> 01:40:36,725
Well, it's a ways, sir.
It's a hike.

1613
01:40:36,804 --> 01:40:39,637
About how far by Jeep?

1614
01:40:39,706 --> 01:40:43,073
About ten or fifteen minutes, sir.

1615
01:40:43,143 --> 01:40:45,043
You ever had to walk it?

1616
01:40:45,112 --> 01:40:48,946
Yes, sir. That day, Friday.
The pickup private-

1617
01:40:49,016 --> 01:40:52,076
That's what we call the guy
who drops us off and picks us up...

1618
01:40:52,152 --> 01:40:55,349
also 'cause he can get girls
in New York City.

1619
01:40:56,390 --> 01:40:58,551
The pickup private got a flat,
sir, right at 39.

1620
01:40:58,625 --> 01:41:01,458
He pulled up and, bam,
blowout with no spare.

1621
01:41:01,528 --> 01:41:03,587
So we had to double-time it
back to the barracks.

1622
01:41:03,664 --> 01:41:07,361
And if it’s about ten or fifteen
minutes by Jeep, I'm guessing...

1623
01:41:07,434 --> 01:41:10,494
it must be a good hour by foot,
am I right?

1624
01:41:10,571 --> 01:41:13,665
Pickup and me did it
in 45 flat, sir.

1625
01:41:13,740 --> 01:41:15,173
Not bad.

1626
01:41:16,610 --> 01:41:20,046
You've said that your assault
on Private Santiago...

1627
01:41:20,114 --> 01:41:23,379
was a result of an order
that Lieutenant Kendrick gave you...

1628
01:41:23,450 --> 01:41:27,011
in your barracks room
at 1620, am I right?

1629
01:41:28,155 --> 01:41:29,747
Yes, sir.

1630
01:41:29,823 --> 01:41:33,623
But you just said that you didn't
make it back to the barracks until 1645.

1631
01:41:34,964 --> 01:41:35,824
Sir?

1632
01:41:36,196 --> 01:41:40,326
Well, if you didn't make it back
to the barracks until 1645...

1633
01:41:40,400 --> 01:41:42,595
how could you be
in your room at 1620?

1634
01:41:43,637 --> 01:41:46,435
Well, you see, sir,
there was a blowout-

1635
01:41:46,507 --> 01:41:50,409
Did you ever actually hear
Lieutenant Kendrick order a Code Red?

1636
01:41:50,477 --> 01:41:52,206
Well, Hal said that-

1637
01:41:52,279 --> 01:41:54,804
Private, did you ever
actually hear...

1638
01:41:54,882 --> 01:41:57,612
Lieutenant Kendrick
order a Code Red?

1639
01:41:57,913 --> 01:41:59,313
No, sir.

1640
01:41:59,386 --> 01:42:02,719
I'd like to request a recess
in order to confer with my client.

1641
01:42:02,789 --> 01:42:05,121
- Why did you go into Santiago's room?
- The witness has rights!

1642
01:42:05,192 --> 01:42:08,457
- The witness has been read his rights.
- The question will be repeated.

1643
01:42:08,529 --> 01:42:10,463
Why did you go
into Santiago's room?

1644
01:42:10,531 --> 01:42:13,967
Did Lance Corporal Dawson tell you
to give Santiago a Code Red?

1645
01:42:14,034 --> 01:42:15,797
- Don't look at him!
- Hal!

1646
01:42:15,869 --> 01:42:17,803
Answer the captain's question!

1647
01:42:21,108 --> 01:42:23,440
Yes, Captain, I was given an order
by my squad leader...

1648
01:42:23,510 --> 01:42:26,843
Lance Corporal Harold W. Dawson,
United States Marine Corps...

1649
01:42:26,914 --> 01:42:28,176
and I followed it.

1650
01:42:49,603 --> 01:42:51,264
Where do you think he is?

1651
01:42:53,540 --> 01:42:56,304
As far as Downey was concerned,
it was an order from Kendrick.

1652
01:42:56,376 --> 01:42:58,344
It doesn't matter that
he didn't hear it firsthand.

1653
01:42:58,412 --> 01:43:01,472
He doesn't distinguish
between the two.

1654
01:43:05,652 --> 01:43:07,950
Danny, I'm sorry.

1655
01:43:08,855 --> 01:43:10,413
Don't worry about it.

1656
01:43:10,490 --> 01:43:13,050
Sam and I were just talking about
how all we really have to do...

1657
01:43:13,126 --> 01:43:15,993
is call some witnesses
who will talk about implied orders.

1658
01:43:16,063 --> 01:43:18,623
Maybe we can put Downey back
on the stand before we get to Dawson.

1659
01:43:19,399 --> 01:43:24,029
If we work at it, we can get Dawson
charged with the Kennedy assassination.

1660
01:43:27,341 --> 01:43:28,501
Are you drunk?

1661
01:43:29,376 --> 01:43:32,140
Pretty much.

1662
01:43:32,212 --> 01:43:34,544
Yeah.

1663
01:43:34,615 --> 01:43:38,176
I'll put on a pot of coffee.
We've got a long night's work ahead.

1664
01:43:39,319 --> 01:43:41,719
She's gonna make coffee.

1665
01:43:42,856 --> 01:43:44,824
That's nice.

1666
01:43:48,762 --> 01:43:51,595
Downey wasn’t in his room.

1667
01:43:51,665 --> 01:43:53,565
Wasn't even there.

1668
01:43:55,002 --> 01:43:58,199
That was an important piece
of information, don’t you think?

1669
01:44:00,674 --> 01:44:04,974
Danny, it was a setback,
and I'm sorry.

1670
01:44:05,045 --> 01:44:07,741
But we fix it,
and move on to Markinson.

1671
01:44:09,483 --> 01:44:11,212
Markinson's dead.

1672
01:44:17,090 --> 01:44:21,117
You really gotta hand it
to those Federal Marshals, boy.

1673
01:44:21,194 --> 01:44:23,856
It's not like he hanged himself
by his shoelaces...

1674
01:44:23,930 --> 01:44:26,558
or slashed his wrists
with a concealed butter knife.

1675
01:44:26,633 --> 01:44:28,066
This guy...

1676
01:44:30,003 --> 01:44:33,666
got into full dress uniform,
stood in the middle of that room...

1677
01:44:33,740 --> 01:44:36,903
drew a nickel-plated pistol
from his holster...

1678
01:44:36,977 --> 01:44:39,377
and fired a bullet into his mouth.

1679
01:44:43,283 --> 01:44:47,151
Anyway, since we seem to be out of
witnesses, I thought I'd drink a little.

1680
01:44:47,220 --> 01:44:49,415
I still think we can win.

1681
01:44:51,458 --> 01:44:53,085
Maybe you should drink a little.

1682
01:44:53,160 --> 01:44:58,154
We'll go to Randolph in the morning and
make a motion for a 24-hour continuance.

1683
01:44:58,231 --> 01:45:01,496
- Why would we want to do that?
- To subpoena Colonel Jessup.

1684
01:45:02,669 --> 01:45:05,433
- What?
- Listen for a second. Hear me out.

1685
01:45:05,434 --> 01:45:07,530
No. I won't listen,
and I won't hear you out.

1686
01:45:07,607 --> 01:45:09,905
Your passion is compelling, Jo.
It's also useless.

1687
01:45:09,976 --> 01:45:13,104
Louden Downey
needed a trial lawyer today.

1688
01:45:16,116 --> 01:45:17,811
You're chickenshit.

1689
01:45:17,884 --> 01:45:20,614
You're gonna use what happened today
as an excuse to give up.

1690
01:45:22,089 --> 01:45:23,681
It's over.

1691
01:45:23,757 --> 01:45:26,317
Why did you ask Jessup
for the transfer order?

1692
01:45:26,393 --> 01:45:29,021
- In Cuba. Why?
- What does it matter?

1693
01:45:29,096 --> 01:45:31,758
- I wanted the damn transfer order!
- Bullshit.

1694
01:45:31,832 --> 01:45:35,324
You could've gotten it by calling
any department at the Pentagon.

1695
01:45:35,402 --> 01:45:40,135
You didn't want the transfer order.
You wanted to see Jessup’s reaction.

1696
01:45:40,207 --> 01:45:43,267
You had an instinct,
and it was confirmed by Markinson.

1697
01:45:43,343 --> 01:45:46,278
Let's put Jessup on the stand
and end this thing!

1698
01:45:46,346 --> 01:45:50,510
What possible good could come
from putting Jessup on the stand?

1699
01:45:50,584 --> 01:45:52,711
He told Kendrick
to order the Code Red.

1700
01:45:52,786 --> 01:45:56,847
He did? That's great!
Why didn’t you say so?

1701
01:45:56,923 --> 01:45:59,187
And of course
you have proof of that!

1702
01:45:59,259 --> 01:46:03,491
Oh, I'm sorry. I forgot. You were sick
the day they taught law at law school.

1703
01:46:03,563 --> 01:46:06,031
You put him on the stand,
and you get it from him.

1704
01:46:06,099 --> 01:46:10,126
Oh, we get it from him!
Yes! No problem!

1705
01:46:10,203 --> 01:46:14,037
Colonel Jessup, isn't it true that
you ordered the Code Red on Santiago?

1706
01:46:14,107 --> 01:46:17,235
- Listen, we're all a little-
- I'm sorry. Your time's run out.

1707
01:46:17,310 --> 01:46:20,404
What do we have for the losers?
Well, for our defendants...

1708
01:46:20,480 --> 01:46:22,846
it's a lifetime
at exotic Fort Leavenworth.

1709
01:46:22,916 --> 01:46:25,885
And for Defense Counsel Kaffee...

1710
01:46:25,952 --> 01:46:27,749
it's a court-martial!

1711
01:46:27,821 --> 01:46:30,984
Yes, Johnny,
after falsely accusing...

1712
01:46:31,057 --> 01:46:33,389
a highly decorated Marine officer...

1713
01:46:33,460 --> 01:46:35,325
of conspiracy and perjury...

1714
01:46:35,395 --> 01:46:38,523
Lieutenant Kaffee will have
a long and prosperous career...

1715
01:46:38,598 --> 01:46:43,831
teaching typewriter maintenance
at the Rocco Clubo School for Women.

1716
01:46:43,904 --> 01:46:46,964
Thank you for playing
"Should we or should we not...

1717
01:46:47,040 --> 01:46:50,100
follow the advice
of the galactically stupid?"

1718
01:47:11,965 --> 01:47:15,025
I'm sorry I lost
your set of steak knives.

1719
01:47:32,018 --> 01:47:33,952
Stop cleaning up.

1720
01:47:39,159 --> 01:47:41,093
Stop cleaning up.

1721
01:47:49,603 --> 01:47:52,538
- Want a drink?
- Yeah.

1722
01:48:10,557 --> 01:48:13,788
- Is your father proud of you?
- Don't do this to yourself.

1723
01:48:13,860 --> 01:48:15,589
I'll bet he is.

1724
01:48:16,396 --> 01:48:19,729
I'll bet he bores the shit
out of the neighbors and relatives.

1725
01:48:19,799 --> 01:48:24,259
"Sam's made Law Review.
He's got a big case he's making.

1726
01:48:24,337 --> 01:48:27,465
He's arguing.
He's making an argument. "

1727
01:48:32,979 --> 01:48:37,211
I think my father would’ve enjoyed
seeing me graduate from law school.

1728
01:48:40,720 --> 01:48:43,416
I think he would've liked that
an awful lot.

1729
01:48:45,992 --> 01:48:48,961
Did I ever tell you I wrote a paper
about your father in college?

1730
01:48:50,030 --> 01:48:51,463
Yeah?

1731
01:48:51,531 --> 01:48:54,125
One of the best
trial lawyers ever.

1732
01:48:54,200 --> 01:48:57,533
Yes, he was.

1733
01:48:57,604 --> 01:48:59,902
If I were Dawson and Downey
and I had a choice...

1734
01:48:59,973 --> 01:49:02,942
between you or your father
to represent me in this case...

1735
01:49:03,009 --> 01:49:06,001
I'd choose you any day of the week
and twice on Sunday.

1736
01:49:06,079 --> 01:49:09,480
You should've seen yourself
thunder away at Kendrick.

1737
01:49:12,586 --> 01:49:14,520
Would you put Jessup on the stand?

1738
01:49:18,258 --> 01:49:22,718
- Do you think my father would have?
- With the evidence we got?

1739
01:49:22,796 --> 01:49:25,697
Not in a million years.

1740
01:49:25,765 --> 01:49:29,132
But here's the thing- and there's
really know way of getting around this-

1741
01:49:29,202 --> 01:49:33,536
Neither Lyle Kaffee nor Sam Weinberg
are lead counsel for the defense...

1742
01:49:33,607 --> 01:49:36,735
in the matter of
U.S. v. Dawson and Downey.

1743
01:49:36,810 --> 01:49:40,746
So there's really only one question-
What would you do?

1744
01:49:52,792 --> 01:49:56,853
Jo, get in the car.
Joanne, please get in the car.

1745
01:49:56,930 --> 01:49:58,363
Look-

1746
01:50:01,835 --> 01:50:06,169
I apologize. I was angry.
I'm sorry about what I said.

1747
01:50:06,239 --> 01:50:08,833
I'm gonna put Jessup on the stand.

1748
01:50:29,095 --> 01:50:30,756
What do you suggest we do?

1749
01:50:30,830 --> 01:50:33,025
I say we hit Jessup
with the phony transfer order.

1750
01:50:33,099 --> 01:50:35,033
What's a transfer order
without a witness?

1751
01:50:35,101 --> 01:50:36,693
- We have a witness.
- A dead witness.

1752
01:50:36,770 --> 01:50:39,671
In the hands of a lesser attorney,
that would be a problem.

1753
01:50:39,739 --> 01:50:42,207
Look at this. Last night
he's swimming in Jack Daniels...

1754
01:50:42,275 --> 01:50:45,005
and now he can leap tall buildings
in a single bound.

1755
01:50:45,078 --> 01:50:48,275
I'm getting my second wind.
Sit down, both of you.

1756
01:50:48,348 --> 01:50:52,876
Good. Jessup told Kendrick
to order the Code Red. Kendrick did.

1757
01:50:52,952 --> 01:50:55,182
Our clients followed the order.
The cover-up isn't our case.

1758
01:50:55,255 --> 01:50:59,885
To win, Jessup needs to tell the court
members that he ordered the Code Red.

1759
01:50:59,959 --> 01:51:03,690
- You think you can get him to say it?
- I think he wants to say it.

1760
01:51:03,763 --> 01:51:06,027
I think he's pissed off
that he's got to hide from us.

1761
01:51:06,099 --> 01:51:09,591
I think he wants to say that he made
a command decision, and that's the end.

1762
01:51:09,669 --> 01:51:12,604
He eats breakfast 300 yards away...

1763
01:51:12,672 --> 01:51:15,971
from 4,000 Cubans
that are trained to kill him.

1764
01:51:16,042 --> 01:51:18,101
No one's gonna tell him
how to run his unit.

1765
01:51:18,178 --> 01:51:21,045
Least of all the Harvard mouth
in his faggoty white uniform.

1766
01:51:21,114 --> 01:51:23,241
I need to shake him,
put him on the defensive...

1767
01:51:23,316 --> 01:51:26,012
and lead him right
where he's dying to go.

1768
01:51:26,086 --> 01:51:29,055
- That's it? That's the plan?
- That's the plan.

1769
01:51:29,122 --> 01:51:32,319
- How are you gonna do it?
- I have no idea.

1770
01:51:32,392 --> 01:51:34,519
- I need my bat.
- Your what?

1771
01:51:34,594 --> 01:51:36,858
I think better with my bat.
Where's my bat?

1772
01:51:36,930 --> 01:51:40,388
- I put it in the closet.
- You put it in the closet?

1773
01:51:40,467 --> 01:51:44,369
- I was tripping on it.
- Don't ever put that bat in the closet.

1774
01:51:44,437 --> 01:51:48,237
- He thinks better with his bat?
- I can understand that.

1775
01:51:59,686 --> 01:52:02,587
Stay here.
I'm going to the office for a while.

1776
01:52:05,125 --> 01:52:07,753
He does think better with that bat.

1777
01:52:30,250 --> 01:52:33,583
Sam, I need you
to do something for me.

1778
01:52:36,790 --> 01:52:40,021
- What's going on?
- Gotta go out to Andrews.

1779
01:53:03,883 --> 01:53:05,817
- Where's Sam?
- He's on his way.

1780
01:53:05,885 --> 01:53:07,819
- Did he get the guys?
- Yeah.

1781
01:53:07,887 --> 01:53:10,879
Listen, can I talk to you
for a second?

1782
01:53:10,957 --> 01:53:13,187
Oh, yeah, sure.

1783
01:53:23,636 --> 01:53:25,297
How you feeling?

1784
01:53:26,706 --> 01:53:30,267
Well, I think Jessup’s
gonna have his hands full today.

1785
01:53:33,012 --> 01:53:34,946
Listen, Danny...

1786
01:53:36,115 --> 01:53:38,549
when you're out there today...

1787
01:53:38,618 --> 01:53:41,781
if you feel like
it's not gonna happen...

1788
01:53:41,855 --> 01:53:44,983
if you feel like
he's not gonna say it...

1789
01:53:45,058 --> 01:53:46,650
don't go for it.

1790
01:53:48,161 --> 01:53:50,391
You could get in trouble.

1791
01:53:50,463 --> 01:53:52,556
I'm special counsel
for Internal Affairs...

1792
01:53:52,632 --> 01:53:55,192
and I'm telling you
you could get in a lot of trouble.

1793
01:53:55,268 --> 01:53:57,259
Wait, Lieutenant Commander Galloway...

1794
01:53:57,337 --> 01:54:01,569
you're not suggesting
that I back off a material witness?

1795
01:54:01,641 --> 01:54:04,838
If you think you can't get him, yeah.

1796
01:54:07,080 --> 01:54:08,741
All rise.

1797
01:54:13,586 --> 01:54:16,578
- Where's Sam?
- He's on his way.

1798
01:54:22,195 --> 01:54:24,789
- Call your first witness.
- Where is he?

1799
01:54:24,864 --> 01:54:27,196
- He'll be here.
- Lieutenant.

1800
01:54:27,267 --> 01:54:28,928
Call your witness.

1801
01:54:35,608 --> 01:54:38,270
Defense calls Colonel Nathan Jessup.

1802
01:54:55,061 --> 01:54:57,894
Colonel Jessup, would you raise
your right hand please, sir?

1803
01:54:57,964 --> 01:55:01,422
Do you solemnly swear that the testimony
you will give in this court-martial...

1804
01:55:01,501 --> 01:55:04,937
will be the truth, the whole truth
and nothing but the truth?

1805
01:55:05,004 --> 01:55:06,403
Yes, I do.

1806
01:55:06,472 --> 01:55:07,939
Have a seat please, sir.

1807
01:55:09,575 --> 01:55:13,033
Would you state your name, rank
and current billet for the record, sir?

1808
01:55:13,112 --> 01:55:16,240
Colonel Nathan R. Jessup,
commanding officer...

1809
01:55:16,316 --> 01:55:19,615
Marine Ground Forces,
Guantanamo Bay, Cuba.

1810
01:55:19,686 --> 01:55:22,018
- Thank you, sir.
- He's not here.

1811
01:55:27,827 --> 01:55:31,388
Colonel, when you learned
of Santiago’s letter to the N.I.S...

1812
01:55:31,464 --> 01:55:34,592
you had a meeting
with your two senior officers.

1813
01:55:34,667 --> 01:55:36,726
- Is that right?
- Yes.

1814
01:55:36,803 --> 01:55:40,398
The platoon commander,
Lieutenant Jonathan Kendrick...

1815
01:55:40,473 --> 01:55:44,136
and the executive officer,
Lieutenant Colonel Matthew Markinson.

1816
01:55:44,210 --> 01:55:45,734
Yes.

1817
01:55:45,812 --> 01:55:50,306
And at present Colonel Markinson
is dead. Is that right?

1818
01:55:50,383 --> 01:55:54,444
Objection. I'd like to know just what
the defense counsel is implying.

1819
01:55:54,520 --> 01:55:57,956
I'm implying simply that at present
Colonel Markinson is not alive.

1820
01:55:58,024 --> 01:56:01,755
Colonel Jessup doesn't need to appear
in court to confirm that information.

1821
01:56:01,828 --> 01:56:04,262
I just wasn't sure the witness was aware
that two days ago...

1822
01:56:04,330 --> 01:56:07,128
the colonel took his own life
with a .45-caliber pistol.

1823
01:56:07,200 --> 01:56:09,668
The witness is aware,
the court is aware...

1824
01:56:09,736 --> 01:56:11,670
and now the court members
are aware.

1825
01:56:11,738 --> 01:56:15,299
We thank you for bringing this
to our attention.

1826
01:56:15,375 --> 01:56:17,104
Move on, Lieutenant..

1827
01:56:17,176 --> 01:56:18,939
Yes, sir.

1828
01:56:19,012 --> 01:56:22,641
Colonel, you gave Lieutenant Kendrick
an order at this meeting, right?

1829
01:56:22,715 --> 01:56:27,049
I told Kendrick to tell his men
that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1830
01:56:27,120 --> 01:56:30,055
And did you give an order
to Colonel Markinson as well?

1831
01:56:30,123 --> 01:56:35,652
I ordered Markinson to have Santiago
transferred off the base immediately.

1832
01:56:35,728 --> 01:56:37,525
Why?

1833
01:56:37,597 --> 01:56:41,363
I felt his life might be in danger
once word of the letter got out.

1834
01:56:41,434 --> 01:56:42,867
Grave danger?

1835
01:56:42,935 --> 01:56:45,130
Is there another kind?

1836
01:56:48,741 --> 01:56:52,677
Colonel, we have the transfer order
that you and Markinson co-signed...

1837
01:56:52,745 --> 01:56:57,375
ordering that Santiago be on a flight
leaving Guantanamo at 6:00 the next morning.

1838
01:56:57,450 --> 01:57:02,547
- Was that the first flight?
- The 0600 was the first flight.

1839
01:57:06,426 --> 01:57:09,793
You flew up to Washington this morning.
Is that right?

1840
01:57:09,862 --> 01:57:13,263
I notice you’re wearing your
class "A" dress uniform in court today.

1841
01:57:13,332 --> 01:57:16,529
- As are you, Lieutenant.
- Did you wear that on the plane?

1842
01:57:16,602 --> 01:57:19,400
Please the court, is this dialogue
relevant to anything-

1843
01:57:19,472 --> 01:57:22,168
Defense didn't have the opportunity
to depose this witness.

1844
01:57:22,241 --> 01:57:25,938
- I'd ask for a little latitude.
- A very little latitude.

1845
01:57:28,181 --> 01:57:30,206
I wore utilities on the plane.

1846
01:57:30,283 --> 01:57:33,343
- You brought your dress uniform?
- Yes.

1847
01:57:33,419 --> 01:57:36,820
- Toothbrush, shaving kit, underwear?
- Your Honor!

1848
01:57:36,889 --> 01:57:39,255
Is the colonel's underwear
a matter of national security?

1849
01:57:39,325 --> 01:57:42,726
Gentlemen! You better get somewhere
fast with this, Lieutenant.

1850
01:57:42,795 --> 01:57:44,854
Yes, sir. Colonel?

1851
01:57:45,965 --> 01:57:49,696
I brought a change of clothes
and some personal items.

1852
01:57:49,769 --> 01:57:51,634
Thank you.

1853
01:57:51,704 --> 01:57:55,367
After Dawson and Downey's arrest
on the night of the sixth...

1854
01:57:55,441 --> 01:57:59,707
Santiago's barracks were sealed off
and its contents inventoried.

1855
01:57:59,779 --> 01:58:03,078
" Four pairs camouflage pants,
three long-sleeve khaki shirts...

1856
01:58:03,149 --> 01:58:07,051
three pairs of boots, four pairs
green socks, three green T-shirts-"

1857
01:58:07,120 --> 01:58:10,055
Please the court, is there a question
anywhere in our future?

1858
01:58:10,123 --> 01:58:13,251
Lieutenant Kaffee, I have to ask you
to state your question.

1859
01:58:13,326 --> 01:58:16,124
I'm wondering why Santiago
wasn't packed.

1860
01:58:18,197 --> 01:58:21,462
I'll tell you what.
We'll get back to that one in a minute.

1861
01:58:22,368 --> 01:58:25,701
This is a record of all phone calls made
from your base in the past 24 hours.

1862
01:58:25,771 --> 01:58:29,366
After being subpoenaed to Washington,
you made three calls.

1863
01:58:29,442 --> 01:58:31,774
Do you recognize
those number, sir?

1864
01:58:31,844 --> 01:58:34,972
I called Colonel Fitzhughes
in Quantico, Virginia.

1865
01:58:35,047 --> 01:58:37,845
I wanted to let him know
that I would be in town.

1866
01:58:37,917 --> 01:58:41,478
The second call was to arrange a meeting
with Congressman Richmond...

1867
01:58:41,554 --> 01:58:43,818
of the House Armed Services Committee.

1868
01:58:43,890 --> 01:58:46,950
And the third call
was to my sister Elizabeth.

1869
01:58:47,026 --> 01:58:49,119
Why did you make that call, sir?

1870
01:58:49,195 --> 01:58:52,596
I thought she might like
to have dinner tonight.

1871
01:58:52,665 --> 01:58:56,032
- I'm gonna stop this.
- These are phone records from Gitmo...

1872
01:58:56,102 --> 01:59:00,334
for September 6,
and these are 14 letters...

1873
01:59:00,406 --> 01:59:03,136
that Santiago wrote in nine months...

1874
01:59:03,209 --> 01:59:06,372
requesting- in fact, begging-
for a transfer.

1875
01:59:06,445 --> 01:59:09,642
Upon hearing the news that
he was finally getting his transfer...

1876
01:59:09,715 --> 01:59:13,674
Santiago was so excited that
do you know how many people he called?

1877
01:59:13,753 --> 01:59:16,221
Zero. Nobody.

1878
01:59:16,289 --> 01:59:20,157
Not one call to his parents
saying he was coming home.

1879
01:59:20,226 --> 01:59:23,457
Not one call to a friend, saying,
"Can you pick me up at the airport?"

1880
01:59:23,529 --> 01:59:27,363
He was asleep in his bed at midnight,
and according to you...

1881
01:59:27,433 --> 01:59:29,958
he was getting on a plane
in six hours.

1882
01:59:30,036 --> 01:59:33,597
Yet everything he owned
was hanging neatly in his closet...

1883
01:59:33,673 --> 01:59:36,301
and folded neatly in his footlocker.

1884
01:59:36,375 --> 01:59:40,141
You were leaving for one day.
You packed a bag and made three calls.

1885
01:59:40,213 --> 01:59:44,547
Santiago was leaving
for the rest of his life...

1886
01:59:46,319 --> 01:59:49,083
and he hadn't called a soul...

1887
01:59:49,155 --> 01:59:51,817
and he hadn't packed a thing.

1888
01:59:55,061 --> 01:59:56,824
Can you explain that?

1889
01:59:59,332 --> 02:00:01,596
The fact is,
there was no transfer order.

1890
02:00:01,667 --> 02:00:04,431
Santiago wasn't going anywhere.
Isn't that right, Colonel?

1891
02:00:04,503 --> 02:00:07,961
Objection. Your Honor, it's obvious
that Lieutenant Kaffee's intention...

1892
02:00:08,040 --> 02:00:10,372
is the smear
a high-ranking Marine officer...

1893
02:00:10,443 --> 02:00:14,106
in the hope that the mere appearance
of impropriety will win him points.

1894
02:00:14,180 --> 02:00:18,116
It's my recommendation, sir,
that Lieutenant Kaffee be reprimanded...

1895
02:00:18,184 --> 02:00:21,085
and the witness be excused
with the court's deepest apologies.

1896
02:00:22,922 --> 02:00:26,016
Overruled.
Your objection is noted.

1897
02:00:32,465 --> 02:00:34,296
Is this funny, sir?

1898
02:00:34,367 --> 02:00:37,700
No, it's not.
It's tragic.

1899
02:00:37,770 --> 02:00:40,466
- Do you have an answer?
- Absolutely.

1900
02:00:40,539 --> 02:00:44,339
My answer is,
I don't have the first damn clue.

1901
02:00:44,410 --> 02:00:48,176
Maybe he was an early riser
and liked to pack in the morning.

1902
02:00:48,247 --> 02:00:51,080
And maybe he didn't have any friends.

1903
02:00:51,150 --> 02:00:54,642
I'm an educated man, but I'm afraid
I can't speak intelligently...

1904
02:00:54,720 --> 02:00:58,383
about the travel habits
of William Santiago.

1905
02:00:58,457 --> 02:01:03,485
What I do know is that he was set
to leave the base at 0600.

1906
02:01:04,363 --> 02:01:09,460
Now, are these really the questions
that I was called here to answer?

1907
02:01:09,535 --> 02:01:11,901
Phone calls and footlockers?

1908
02:01:11,971 --> 02:01:15,668
Please tell me that you have
something more, Lieutenant.

1909
02:01:15,741 --> 02:01:19,507
These two Marines
are on trial for their lives.

1910
02:01:19,578 --> 02:01:24,015
Please tell me that their lawyer hasn't
pinned their hopes to a phone bill.

1911
02:01:26,519 --> 02:01:29,955
Do you have any other questions
for me, counselor?

1912
02:01:48,708 --> 02:01:52,235
Lieutenant, do you have anything
further for this witness?

1913
02:01:59,752 --> 02:02:02,016
Thanks, Danny.
I love Washington.

1914
02:02:02,088 --> 02:02:04,682
Excuse me.
I didn't dismiss you.

1915
02:02:05,758 --> 02:02:07,521
I beg your pardon?

1916
02:02:07,593 --> 02:02:12,121
I'm not through with my examination.
Sit down.

1917
02:02:13,833 --> 02:02:16,597
- Colonel.
- What's that?

1918
02:02:16,669 --> 02:02:19,331
I'd appreciate it if you’d address me
as "colonel" or "sir. "

1919
02:02:19,405 --> 02:02:20,997
I believe I've earned it.

1920
02:02:21,073 --> 02:02:25,305
Defense counsel will address
the witness as "colonel" or "sir. "

1921
02:02:25,378 --> 02:02:28,347
I don't know what the hell
kind of unit you're running here.

1922
02:02:28,414 --> 02:02:32,214
The witness will address this court
as "judge" or "your honor. "

1923
02:02:32,284 --> 02:02:37,017
I'm quite certain I've earned it.
Take your seat, Colonel.

1924
02:02:41,994 --> 02:02:46,090
What do you want to discuss now?
My favorite color?

1925
02:02:47,366 --> 02:02:50,062
Colonel, the 6:00 a. m. flight
was the first one off the base?

1926
02:02:50,136 --> 02:02:51,194
Yes.

1927
02:02:51,270 --> 02:02:53,329
There wasn't a flight
that left seven hours earlier...

1928
02:02:53,406 --> 02:02:55,738
and landed at Andrews Air Force Base
at 2:00 a. m.?

1929
02:02:55,808 --> 02:02:58,777
Lieutenant, I think
we've covered this, haven't we?

1930
02:02:59,812 --> 02:03:01,939
Your Honor, these are
the tower chief’s logs...

1931
02:03:02,014 --> 02:03:04,847
for both Guantanamo Bay
and Andrews Air Force Base.

1932
02:03:04,917 --> 02:03:08,284
The Guantanamo log lists no flight
that left at 11:00 p. m.

1933
02:03:08,354 --> 02:03:10,948
The Andrews log lists no flight
that landed at 2:00 a. m.

1934
02:03:11,023 --> 02:03:13,617
I'd like to admit them
as defense exhibits Alpha and Bravo.

1935
02:03:14,393 --> 02:03:17,920
I don't understand. You're admitting
evidence of a flight that never existed.

1936
02:03:17,997 --> 02:03:20,465
We believe it did, sir.

1937
02:03:20,533 --> 02:03:23,832
Defense will be calling Airmen
Cecil O'Malley and Anthony Rodriguez.

1938
02:03:23,903 --> 02:03:26,929
They were working the ground crew
at Andrews at 2:00 a. m. on the 7th.

1939
02:03:27,006 --> 02:03:29,839
- These men weren't on the list.
- Rebuttal witnesses, Your Honor...

1940
02:03:29,909 --> 02:03:34,243
called specifically to refute testimony
offered under direct examination.

1941
02:03:34,313 --> 02:03:37,282
- I'll allow the witnesses.
- This is ridiculous.

1942
02:03:37,349 --> 02:03:41,752
- Colonel, a moment ago-
- Check the tower logs, for Christ's sake!

1943
02:03:42,721 --> 02:03:44,916
We'll get to the airmen
in just a minute, sir.

1944
02:03:45,958 --> 02:03:47,892
A moment ago you said that
you ordered Lieutenant Kendrick...

1945
02:03:47,960 --> 02:03:51,987
to tell his men
that Santiago wasn't to be touched.

1946
02:03:52,064 --> 02:03:53,622
That's right.

1947
02:03:53,699 --> 02:03:56,429
And Lieutenant Kendrick was clear
on what you wanted?

1948
02:03:56,502 --> 02:03:58,299
Crystal.

1949
02:03:58,370 --> 02:04:01,498
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick
ignored the order?

1950
02:04:01,574 --> 02:04:03,565
Ignored the order?

1951
02:04:03,642 --> 02:04:06,736
Any chance he forgot about it?

1952
02:04:06,812 --> 02:04:10,942
Any chance Lieutenant Kendrick left your
office and said, "The old man is wrong"?

1953
02:04:12,985 --> 02:04:15,249
When Lieutenant Kendrick
spoke to the platoon...

1954
02:04:15,321 --> 02:04:18,586
and ordered them not to touch Santiago,
any chance they ignored him?

1955
02:04:20,025 --> 02:04:23,017
You ever served
in an infantry unit, son?

1956
02:04:23,095 --> 02:04:26,394
- No, sir.
- Ever served in a forward area?

1957
02:04:27,733 --> 02:04:30,759
Ever put your life
in another man's hands?

1958
02:04:30,836 --> 02:04:33,464
Asked him to put his life in yours?

1959
02:04:34,740 --> 02:04:36,708
We follow orders, son.

1960
02:04:36,775 --> 02:04:39,744
We follow orders, or people die.

1961
02:04:39,812 --> 02:04:42,975
It's that simple.
Are we clear?

1962
02:04:43,048 --> 02:04:44,879
Yes, sir.

1963
02:04:44,950 --> 02:04:46,679
Are we clear?

1964
02:04:46,752 --> 02:04:48,686
Crystal.

1965
02:04:50,823 --> 02:04:55,385
I have just one more question before
I call Airmen O'Malley and Rodriguez.

1966
02:04:56,729 --> 02:05:00,995
If you gave an order
that Santiago wasn't to be touched...

1967
02:05:01,066 --> 02:05:03,591
and your orders
are always followed...

1968
02:05:05,571 --> 02:05:08,665
then why would Santiago
be in danger?

1969
02:05:10,576 --> 02:05:14,307
Why would it be necessary
to transfer him off the base?

1970
02:05:19,919 --> 02:05:23,047
Santiago was a substandard Marine.

1971
02:05:23,122 --> 02:05:25,522
- He was being transferred-
- That's not what you said!

1972
02:05:25,591 --> 02:05:29,220
You said he was being transferred
because he was in grave danger.

1973
02:05:29,295 --> 02:05:32,230
I said, "Grave danger?"
You said, "Is there any other kind?"

1974
02:05:32,298 --> 02:05:34,823
- I recall what I said.
- I can have it read back to you.

1975
02:05:34,900 --> 02:05:37,892
I know what I said!
I don't have to have it read back to me.

1976
02:05:37,970 --> 02:05:41,565
Then why the two orders?
Colonel?

1977
02:05:43,509 --> 02:05:46,205
Sometimes men take matters
into their own hands.

1978
02:05:46,278 --> 02:05:49,372
You've made it clear that your men
never take matters into their own hands.

1979
02:05:49,448 --> 02:05:51,416
Your men follow orders,
or people die.

1980
02:05:51,483 --> 02:05:54,111
So Santiago should have been
in danger, should he?

1981
02:05:54,186 --> 02:05:58,054
- You snotty little bastard.
- I'd like to ask for a recess.

1982
02:05:58,123 --> 02:06:01,752
- I'd like an answer to the question.
- The court will wait for an answer.

1983
02:06:02,595 --> 02:06:04,927
If Lieutenant Kendrick
gave an order...

1984
02:06:04,997 --> 02:06:07,966
that Santiago
wasn't to be touched...

1985
02:06:08,033 --> 02:06:09,967
then why did he
have to be transferred?

1986
02:06:12,871 --> 02:06:17,069
Lieutenant Kendrick ordered the Code Red
because that's what you told him to do!

1987
02:06:17,142 --> 02:06:20,134
- Object!
- And then you cut these guys loose!

1988
02:06:20,212 --> 02:06:23,773
- I'll hold you in contempt.
- You doctored the logbook!

1989
02:06:23,849 --> 02:06:26,716
- Damn it, Kaffee!
- Consider yourself in contempt.

1990
02:06:26,785 --> 02:06:29,583
Colonel Jessup,
did you order the Code Red?

1991
02:06:29,655 --> 02:06:33,216
- You don't have to answer that.
- I'll answer the question.

1992
02:06:33,292 --> 02:06:35,317
- You want answers?
- I think I'm entitled!

1993
02:06:35,394 --> 02:06:37,794
- You want answers?
- I want the truth!

1994
02:06:37,863 --> 02:06:40,957
You can't handle the truth!

1995
02:06:41,033 --> 02:06:43,024
Son, we live in a world
that has walls...

1996
02:06:43,102 --> 02:06:45,730
and those walls have to be guarded
by men with guns.

1997
02:06:45,804 --> 02:06:50,173
Who's gonna do it? You?
You, Lieutenant Weinberg?

1998
02:06:50,242 --> 02:06:54,235
I have a greater responsibility
than you can possibly fathom.

1999
02:06:54,313 --> 02:06:57,771
You weep for Santiago,
and you curse the Marines.

2000
02:06:57,850 --> 02:07:01,684
You have the luxury
of not knowing what I know-

2001
02:07:01,754 --> 02:07:05,850
that Santiago's death,
while tragic, probably saved lives.

2002
02:07:05,924 --> 02:07:11,829
And my existence, while grotesque and
incomprehensible to you, saves lives!

2003
02:07:11,897 --> 02:07:16,027
You don't want the truth because
deep down you don't talk about...

2004
02:07:16,101 --> 02:07:18,262
you want me on that wall.

2005
02:07:18,337 --> 02:07:21,033
You need me on that wall!

2006
02:07:21,106 --> 02:07:25,770
We use words
like honor, code, loyalty.

2007
02:07:25,844 --> 02:07:29,541
We use these words as the backbone
of a life spent defending something.

2008
02:07:29,615 --> 02:07:31,606
You use them as a punch line.

2009
02:07:31,684 --> 02:07:35,518
I have neither the time
nor the inclination to explain myself...

2010
02:07:35,587 --> 02:07:39,751
to a man who rises and sleeps under
the blanket of the freedom I provide...

2011
02:07:39,825 --> 02:07:42,692
and then questions the manner
in which I provide it!

2012
02:07:42,761 --> 02:07:46,026
I would rather you just said thank you
and went on your way.

2013
02:07:46,098 --> 02:07:49,864
Otherwise, I suggest you
pick up a weapon and stand a post.

2014
02:07:49,935 --> 02:07:54,838
Either way, I don't give a damn
what you think you are entitled to!

2015
02:07:54,907 --> 02:07:56,568
Did you order the Code Red?

2016
02:07:56,642 --> 02:07:58,576
- I did the job-
- Did you order the Code Red?

2017
02:07:58,644 --> 02:08:00,976
You're goddamned right I did!

2018
02:08:12,024 --> 02:08:15,118
Please the court,
I suggest the members be dismissed...

2019
02:08:15,194 --> 02:08:18,425
so that we can move to an immediate
Article 39-A session.

2020
02:08:18,497 --> 02:08:20,931
The witness has rights.

2021
02:08:20,999 --> 02:08:23,229
Captain Ross?

2022
02:08:34,113 --> 02:08:37,776
The members of the court will retire
to an anteroom until further instructed.

2023
02:08:37,850 --> 02:08:39,647
All rise.

2024
02:08:40,886 --> 02:08:44,378
What the hell is this?
Colonel, what's going on?

2025
02:08:44,456 --> 02:08:46,981
I did my job.
I'd do it again.

2026
02:08:47,059 --> 02:08:50,187
I'm gonna get on a plane
and go on back to my base.

2027
02:08:50,262 --> 02:08:53,959
You're not going anywhere, Colonel.
M.P.s, guard the colonel.

2028
02:08:54,032 --> 02:08:55,465
Yes, sir.

2029
02:08:57,503 --> 02:09:00,028
- Captain Ross.
- What the hell is this?

2030
02:09:00,105 --> 02:09:03,006
Colonel Jessup, you have
the right to remain silent.

2031
02:09:03,075 --> 02:09:07,705
I'm being charged with a crime?
Is that what this is?

2032
02:09:07,780 --> 02:09:11,113
- I'm being charged with a crime?
- You have a right to consult a lawyer.

2033
02:09:11,183 --> 02:09:15,017
- This is funny. That's what this is.
- This lawyer may be appointed by you.

2034
02:09:15,087 --> 02:09:18,784
I'm gonna rip the eyes out of your head
and piss in your dead skull!

2035
02:09:18,857 --> 02:09:20,791
You fucked with the wrong Marine!

2036
02:09:20,859 --> 02:09:24,260
Colonel Jessup, do you understand
these rights as I have just read them?

2037
02:09:30,502 --> 02:09:33,266
You fucking people.

2038
02:09:33,338 --> 02:09:36,102
You have no idea
how to defend a nation.

2039
02:09:36,175 --> 02:09:39,611
All you did was weaken
a country today, Kaffee.

2040
02:09:39,678 --> 02:09:41,669
That's all you did.

2041
02:09:41,747 --> 02:09:46,844
You put people's lives in danger.
Sweet dreams, son.

2042
02:09:46,919 --> 02:09:49,080
Don't call me son.

2043
02:09:49,154 --> 02:09:53,591
I'm a lawyer and an officer
in the United States Navy...

2044
02:09:53,659 --> 02:09:56,423
and you're under arrest,
you son of a bitch.

2045
02:10:00,732 --> 02:10:02,700
The witness is excused.

2046
02:10:24,823 --> 02:10:25,881
All rise.

2047
02:10:37,402 --> 02:10:39,029
Have the members reached a verdict?

2048
02:10:39,104 --> 02:10:41,038
We have, sir.

2049
02:10:52,851 --> 02:10:56,309
Lance Corporal Dawson
and Private First Class Downey.

2050
02:10:59,691 --> 02:11:03,855
On the charge of murder,
the members find the accused...

2051
02:11:03,929 --> 02:11:05,863
not guilty.

2052
02:11:06,932 --> 02:11:10,527
On the charge
of conspiracy to commit murder...

2053
02:11:10,602 --> 02:11:14,368
the members find the accused
not guilty.

2054
02:11:17,175 --> 02:11:21,009
On the charge of conduct
unbecoming a United States Marine...

2055
02:11:21,079 --> 02:11:26,881
the members find the accused
guilty as charged.

2056
02:11:28,854 --> 02:11:32,017
The accused are hereby sentenced
to time already served...

2057
02:11:32,090 --> 02:11:36,959
and you are ordered to be dishonorably
discharged from the Marine Corps.

2058
02:11:38,363 --> 02:11:40,456
This court-martial is adjourned.

2059
02:11:40,532 --> 02:11:42,432
All rise.

2060
02:11:58,250 --> 02:12:00,218
What does that mean?

2061
02:12:02,219 --> 02:12:03,219
Hal?

2062
02:12:05,390 --> 02:12:07,324
What did that mean?

2063
02:12:10,629 --> 02:12:14,827
I don't understand. Colonel Jessup
said he ordered the Code Red.

2064
